<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="P1" checkit-title="Sample Spaces">
    <statement>
        <p>
Suppose you have 2 spinners that have 6 and 5 equally sized spaces, respectively. Write out the sample space that corresponds to this situation. What is the probability that the first spinner lands on an odd number?
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
        The sample space is
        </p>
        <me>
\begin{array} {lllll} \{(1,1), &amp; (1,2), &amp; (1,3), &amp; (1,4), &amp; (1,5), \\ (2,1), &amp; (2,2), &amp; (2,3), &amp; (2,4), &amp; (2,5), \\ (3,1), &amp; (3,2), &amp; (3,3), &amp; (3,4), &amp; (3,5), \\ (4,1), &amp; (4,2), &amp; (4,3), &amp; (4,4), &amp; (4,5), \\ (5,1), &amp; (5,2), &amp; (5,3), &amp; (5,4), &amp; (5,5), \\ (6,1), &amp; (6,2), &amp; (6,3), &amp; (6,4), &amp; (6,5) \}\end{array}
        </me>
        <p>
        The probability is 15/30.
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
